flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: New or updated production order for engine block machining received from SAP S/4HANA (quantity, due date, and routing constraints).]
  A --> N1[Stream: STREAMS - Ingest production order and master data]
  N1 --> N2[PB: Rules - Evaluate machine/tool availability and apply sequencing rules]
  N2 --> N3{PB: IF - Decision branching for selected route}
  N3 -->|Primary| N4[PB: Transaction - Commit schedule and create shop work order]
  N4 --> N5[PB: UI Screen - Publish work instructions and QC checkpoints to operators]
  N5 --> N6[PB: Notification - Notify stakeholders and record execution report]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Optimized machining routes dispatched to shop floor, updated production orders in SAP S/4HANA, reduced COGS via improved machine utilization and reduced rework, and traceable QC checkpoints for each lot.]
  N3 -->|Required machine(s) unavailable for t...| B1[Rules node routes to alternate machining cell or defers to next available slot; Transaction updates SAP with revised schedule]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Routing adjusted to maintain throughput with minimal COGS impact; scheduler and operators notified]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Tooling shortage or mismatch detected| B2[Process triggers tooling reservation attempt; if unavailable, Branch node flags exception and creates Action Item for tool procurement or re-sequencing]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Avoid machining with improper tooling; either procurement initiated or sequence changed to use available tooling]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Quality tolerance conflict (design vs...| B3[Rules node flags exception and creates CWB Lifecycle-style Action Item for engineering review (manual override or updated process parameters)]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Ensure only compliant routings proceed; prevents out-of-spec production and costly rework]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]